{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":817,"text":"Chris Anderson: You were something\nof a mathematical phenom."},{"time":3675,"text":"You had already taught at Harvard\nand MIT at a young age."},{"time":6763,"text":"And then the NSA came calling."},{"time":9464,"text":"What was that about?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":11207,"text":"Jim Simons: Well the NSA --\nthat's the National Security Agency --"},{"time":15154,"text":"they didn't exactly come calling."},{"time":17465,"text":"They had an operation at Princeton,\nwhere they hired mathematicians"},{"time":21963,"text":"to attack secret codes\nand stuff like that."},{"time":25294,"text":"And I knew that existed."},{"time":27315,"text":"And they had a very good policy,"},{"time":29519,"text":"because you could do half your time\nat your own mathematics,"},{"time":33393,"text":"and at least half your time\nworking on their stuff."},{"time":37559,"text":"And they paid a lot."},{"time":39057,"text":"So that was an irresistible pull."},{"time":42132,"text":"So, I went there."}]},{"cues":[{"time":44068,"text":"CA: You were a code-cracker."}]},{"cues":[{"time":45430,"text":"JS: I was."}]},{"cues":[{"time":46620,"text":"CA: Until you got fired."}]},{"cues":[{"time":47801,"text":"JS: Well, I did get fired. Yes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":49408,"text":"CA: How come?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":51280,"text":"JS: Well, how come?"},{"time":53611,"text":"I got fired because,\nwell, the Vietnam War was on,"},{"time":58591,"text":"and the boss of bosses in my organization\nwas a big fan of the war"},{"time":64353,"text":"and wrote a New York Times article,\na magazine section cover story,"},{"time":68772,"text":"about how we would win in Vietnam."},{"time":70566,"text":"And I didn't like that war,\nI thought it was stupid."},{"time":73719,"text":"And I wrote a letter to the Times,\nwhich they published,"},{"time":76408,"text":"saying not everyone\nwho works for Maxwell Taylor,"},{"time":80446,"text":"if anyone remembers that name,\nagrees with his views."},{"time":85553,"text":"And I gave my own views ..."}]},{"cues":[{"time":87235,"text":"CA: Oh, OK. I can see that would --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":89423,"text":"JS: ... which were different\nfrom General Taylor's."},{"time":92002,"text":"But in the end, nobody said anything."},{"time":93932,"text":"But then, I was 29 years old at this time,\nand some kid came around"},{"time":97657,"text":"and said he was a stringer\nfrom Newsweek magazine"},{"time":100769,"text":"and he wanted to interview me\nand ask what I was doing about my views."},{"time":106160,"text":"And I told him, \"I'm doing\nmostly mathematics now,"},{"time":110083,"text":"and when the war is over,\nthen I'll do mostly their stuff.\""},{"time":114123,"text":"Then I did the only\nintelligent thing I'd done that day --"},{"time":116972,"text":"I told my local boss\nthat I gave that interview."},{"time":121153,"text":"And he said, \"What'd you say?\""},{"time":122636,"text":"And I told him what I said."},{"time":124126,"text":"And then he said,\n\"I've got to call Taylor.\""},{"time":126465,"text":"He called Taylor; that took 10 minutes."},{"time":128866,"text":"I was fired five minutes after that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":131590,"text":"CA: OK."}]},{"cues":[{"time":132836,"text":"JS: But it wasn't bad."}]},{"cues":[{"time":134011,"text":"CA: It wasn't bad,\nbecause you went on to Stony Brook"},{"time":136528,"text":"and stepped up your mathematical career."},{"time":139685,"text":"You started working with this man here."},{"time":142161,"text":"Who is this?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":144352,"text":"JS: Oh, [Shiing-Shen] Chern."},{"time":145788,"text":"Chern was one of the great\nmathematicians of the century."},{"time":148916,"text":"I had known him when\nI was a graduate student at Berkeley."},{"time":154173,"text":"And I had some ideas,"},{"time":156068,"text":"and I brought them to him\nand he liked them."},{"time":158539,"text":"Together, we did this work\nwhich you can easily see up there."},{"time":165189,"text":"There it is."}]},{"cues":[{"time":167198,"text":"CA: It led to you publishing\na famous paper together."},{"time":170828,"text":"Can you explain at all what that work was?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":175028,"text":"JS: No."}]},{"cues":[{"time":176210,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":178966,"text":"JS: I mean, I could\nexplain it to somebody."}]},{"cues":[{"time":181054,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":183153,"text":"CA: How about explaining this?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":185041,"text":"JS: But not many. Not many people."}]},{"cues":[{"time":189144,"text":"CA: I think you told me\nit had something to do with spheres,"},{"time":191982,"text":"so let's start here."}]},{"cues":[{"time":193868,"text":"JS: Well, it did,\nbut I'll say about that work --"},{"time":197492,"text":"it did have something to do with that,\nbut before we get to that --"},{"time":200716,"text":"that work was good mathematics."},{"time":204280,"text":"I was very happy with it; so was Chern."},{"time":207910,"text":"It even started a little sub-field\nthat's now flourishing."},{"time":212638,"text":"But, more interestingly,\nit happened to apply to physics,"},{"time":217956,"text":"something we knew nothing about --\nat least I knew nothing about physics,"},{"time":222275,"text":"and I don't think Chern\nknew a heck of a lot."},{"time":224581,"text":"And about 10 years\nafter the paper came out,"},{"time":228568,"text":"a guy named Ed Witten in Princeton\nstarted applying it to string theory"},{"time":233072,"text":"and people in Russia started applying it\nto what's called \"condensed matter.\""},{"time":237948,"text":"Today, those things in there\ncalled Chern-Simons invariants"},{"time":242865,"text":"have spread through a lot of physics."},{"time":244754,"text":"And it was amazing."},{"time":245952,"text":"We didn't know any physics."},{"time":247714,"text":"It never occurred to me\nthat it would be applied to physics."},{"time":250592,"text":"But that's the thing about mathematics --\nyou never know where it's going to go."}]},{"cues":[{"time":254404,"text":"CA: This is so incredible."},{"time":255920,"text":"So, we've been talking about\nhow evolution shapes human minds"},{"time":260308,"text":"that may or may not perceive the truth."},{"time":262840,"text":"Somehow, you come up\nwith a mathematical theory,"},{"time":266177,"text":"not knowing any physics,"},{"time":268049,"text":"discover two decades later\nthat it's being applied"},{"time":270571,"text":"to profoundly describe\nthe actual physical world."},{"time":273626,"text":"How can that happen?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":274803,"text":"JS: God knows."}]},{"cues":[{"time":275984,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":278849,"text":"But there's a famous physicist\nnamed [Eugene] Wigner,"},{"time":282023,"text":"and he wrote an essay on the unreasonable\neffectiveness of mathematics."},{"time":287635,"text":"Somehow, this mathematics,\nwhich is rooted in the real world"},{"time":291611,"text":"in some sense -- we learn to count,\nmeasure, everyone would do that --"},{"time":296630,"text":"and then it flourishes on its own."},{"time":298976,"text":"But so often it comes\nback to save the day."},{"time":302293,"text":"General relativity is an example."},{"time":304495,"text":"[Hermann] Minkowski had this geometry,\nand Einstein realized,"},{"time":307636,"text":"\"Hey! It's the very thing\nin which I can cast general relativity.\""},{"time":311507,"text":"So, you never know. It is a mystery."},{"time":315056,"text":"It is a mystery."}]},{"cues":[{"time":316297,"text":"CA: So, here's a mathematical\npiece of ingenuity."},{"time":319617,"text":"Tell us about this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":320983,"text":"JS: Well, that's a ball -- it's a sphere,\nand it has a lattice around it --"},{"time":326931,"text":"you know, those squares."},{"time":330697,"text":"What I'm going to show here was\noriginally observed by [Leonhard] Euler,"},{"time":335627,"text":"the great mathematician, in the 1700s."},{"time":338223,"text":"And it gradually grew to be\na very important field in mathematics:"},{"time":343428,"text":"algebraic topology, geometry."},{"time":347039,"text":"That paper up there had its roots in this."},{"time":351427,"text":"So, here's this thing:"},{"time":353285,"text":"it has eight vertices,\n12 edges, six faces."},{"time":357761,"text":"And if you look at the difference --\nvertices minus edges plus faces --"},{"time":361615,"text":"you get two."},{"time":362791,"text":"OK, well, two. That's a good number."},{"time":365034,"text":"Here's a different way of doing it --\nthese are triangles covering --"},{"time":369306,"text":"this has 12 vertices and 30 edges"},{"time":373907,"text":"and 20 faces, 20 tiles."},{"time":378576,"text":"And vertices minus edges\nplus faces still equals two."},{"time":383191,"text":"And in fact, you could do this\nany which way --"},{"time":386062,"text":"cover this thing with all kinds\nof polygons and triangles"},{"time":389484,"text":"and mix them up."},{"time":390828,"text":"And you take vertices minus edges\nplus faces -- you'll get two."},{"time":394131,"text":"Here's a different shape."},{"time":396480,"text":"This is a torus, or the surface\nof a doughnut: 16 vertices"},{"time":401754,"text":"covered by these rectangles,\n32 edges, 16 faces."},{"time":406530,"text":"Vertices minus edges comes out to be zero."},{"time":409238,"text":"It'll always come out to zero."},{"time":410737,"text":"Every time you cover a torus\nwith squares or triangles"},{"time":415071,"text":"or anything like that,\nyou're going to get zero."},{"time":420514,"text":"So, this is called\nthe Euler characteristic."},{"time":422928,"text":"And it's what's called\na topological invariant."},{"time":426849,"text":"It's pretty amazing."},{"time":428029,"text":"No matter how you do it,\nyou're always get the same answer."},{"time":430844,"text":"So that was the first sort of thrust,\nfrom the mid-1700s,"},{"time":437167,"text":"into a subject which is now called\nalgebraic topology."}]},{"cues":[{"time":440960,"text":"CA: And your own work\ntook an idea like this and moved it"},{"time":443967,"text":"into higher-dimensional theory,"},{"time":446440,"text":"higher-dimensional objects,\nand found new invariances?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":449552,"text":"JS: Yes. Well, there were already\nhigher-dimensional invariants:"},{"time":454219,"text":"Pontryagin classes --\nactually, there were Chern classes."},{"time":458700,"text":"There were a bunch\nof these types of invariants."},{"time":462272,"text":"I was struggling to work on one of them"},{"time":466431,"text":"and model it sort of combinatorially,"},{"time":470658,"text":"instead of the way it was typically done,"},{"time":473704,"text":"and that led to this work\nand we uncovered some new things."},{"time":478087,"text":"But if it wasn't for Mr. Euler --"},{"time":481612,"text":"who wrote almost 70 volumes of mathematics"},{"time":485617,"text":"and had 13 children,"},{"time":487372,"text":"who he apparently would dandle on his knee\nwhile he was writing --"},{"time":493838,"text":"if it wasn't for Mr. Euler, there wouldn't\nperhaps be these invariants."}]},{"cues":[{"time":500157,"text":"CA: OK, so that's at least given us\na flavor of that amazing mind in there."},{"time":504804,"text":"Let's talk about Renaissance."},{"time":506371,"text":"Because you took that amazing mind\nand having been a code-cracker at the NSA,"},{"time":512251,"text":"you started to become a code-cracker\nin the financial industry."},{"time":515504,"text":"I think you probably didn't buy\nefficient market theory."},{"time":518218,"text":"Somehow you found a way of creating\nastonishing returns over two decades."},{"time":524629,"text":"The way it's been explained to me,"},{"time":526324,"text":"what's remarkable about what you did\nwasn't just the size of the returns,"},{"time":529847,"text":"it's that you took them\nwith surprisingly low volatility and risk,"},{"time":533754,"text":"compared with other hedge funds."},{"time":535602,"text":"So how on earth did you do this, Jim?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":538071,"text":"JS: I did it by assembling\na wonderful group of people."},{"time":542206,"text":"When I started doing trading, I had\ngotten a little tired of mathematics."},{"time":546186,"text":"I was in my late 30s,\nI had a little money."},{"time":550133,"text":"I started trading and it went very well."},{"time":553063,"text":"I made quite a lot of money\nwith pure luck."},{"time":555835,"text":"I mean, I think it was pure luck."},{"time":557525,"text":"It certainly wasn't mathematical modeling."},{"time":559658,"text":"But in looking at the data,\nafter a while I realized:"},{"time":563513,"text":"it looks like there's some structure here."},{"time":566090,"text":"And I hired a few mathematicians,\nand we started making some models --"},{"time":569811,"text":"just the kind of thing we did back\nat IDA [Institute for Defense Analyses]."},{"time":574100,"text":"You design an algorithm,\nyou test it out on a computer."},{"time":576957,"text":"Does it work? Doesn't it work? And so on."}]},{"cues":[{"time":579443,"text":"CA: Can we take a look at this?"},{"time":580946,"text":"Because here's a typical graph\nof some commodity."},{"time":586487,"text":"I look at that, and I say,\n\"That's just a random, up-and-down walk --"},{"time":590552,"text":"maybe a slight upward trend\nover that whole period of time.\""},{"time":593438,"text":"How on earth could you trade\nlooking at that,"},{"time":595575,"text":"and see something that wasn't just random?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":597925,"text":"JS: In the old days -- this is\nkind of a graph from the old days,"},{"time":601196,"text":"commodities or currencies\nhad a tendency to trend."},{"time":605504,"text":"Not necessarily the very light trend\nyou see here, but trending in periods."},{"time":611583,"text":"And if you decided, OK,\nI'm going to predict today,"},{"time":615663,"text":"by the average move in the past 20 days --"},{"time":620655,"text":"maybe that would be a good prediction,\nand I'd make some money."},{"time":623786,"text":"And in fact, years ago,\nsuch a system would work --"},{"time":629418,"text":"not beautifully, but it would work."},{"time":631833,"text":"You'd make money, you'd lose\nmoney, you'd make money."},{"time":634366,"text":"But this is a year's worth of days,"},{"time":636588,"text":"and you'd make a little money\nduring that period."},{"time":641884,"text":"It's a very vestigial system."}]},{"cues":[{"time":644525,"text":"CA: So you would test\na bunch of lengths of trends in time"},{"time":648078,"text":"and see whether, for example,"},{"time":650538,"text":"a 10-day trend or a 15-day trend\nwas predictive of what happened next."}]},{"cues":[{"time":654043,"text":"JS: Sure, you would try all those things\nand see what worked best."},{"time":661515,"text":"Trend-following would\nhave been great in the '60s,"},{"time":664889,"text":"and it was sort of OK in the '70s."},{"time":667045,"text":"By the '80s, it wasn't."}]},{"cues":[{"time":668942,"text":"CA: Because everyone could see that."},{"time":671783,"text":"So, how did you stay ahead of the pack?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":675046,"text":"JS: We stayed ahead of the pack\nby finding other approaches --"},{"time":681202,"text":"shorter-term approaches to some extent."},{"time":685107,"text":"The real thing was to gather\na tremendous amount of data --"},{"time":688478,"text":"and we had to get it by hand\nin the early days."},{"time":692080,"text":"We went down to the Federal Reserve\nand copied interest rate histories"},{"time":695570,"text":"and stuff like that,\nbecause it didn't exist on computers."},{"time":698859,"text":"We got a lot of data."},{"time":700526,"text":"And very smart people -- that was the key."},{"time":705463,"text":"I didn't really know how to hire\npeople to do fundamental trading."},{"time":709749,"text":"I had hired a few -- some made money,\nsome didn't make money."},{"time":712722,"text":"I couldn't make a business out of that."},{"time":714626,"text":"But I did know how to hire scientists,"},{"time":716692,"text":"because I have some taste\nin that department."},{"time":720105,"text":"So, that's what we did."},{"time":721967,"text":"And gradually these models\ngot better and better,"},{"time":725222,"text":"and better and better."}]},{"cues":[{"time":726581,"text":"CA: You're credited with doing\nsomething remarkable at Renaissance,"},{"time":729819,"text":"which is building this culture,\nthis group of people,"},{"time":732444,"text":"who weren't just hired guns\nwho could be lured away by money."},{"time":735610,"text":"Their motivation was doing\nexciting mathematics and science."}]},{"cues":[{"time":739860,"text":"JS: Well, I'd hoped that might be true."},{"time":742283,"text":"But some of it was money."}]},{"cues":[{"time":745887,"text":"CA: They made a lot of money."}]},{"cues":[{"time":747304,"text":"JS: I can't say that no one came\nbecause of the money."},{"time":749865,"text":"I think a lot of them\ncame because of the money."},{"time":752142,"text":"But they also came\nbecause it would be fun."}]},{"cues":[{"time":754187,"text":"CA: What role did machine learning\nplay in all this?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":756699,"text":"JS: In a certain sense,\nwhat we did was machine learning."},{"time":760879,"text":"You look at a lot of data, and you try\nto simulate different predictive schemes,"},{"time":767194,"text":"until you get better and better at it."},{"time":769400,"text":"It doesn't necessarily feed back on itself\nthe way we did things."},{"time":773191,"text":"But it worked."}]},{"cues":[{"time":776150,"text":"CA: So these different predictive schemes\ncan be really quite wild and unexpected."},{"time":780233,"text":"I mean, you looked at everything, right?"},{"time":782171,"text":"You looked at the weather,\nlength of dresses, political opinion."}]},{"cues":[{"time":785512,"text":"JS: Yes, length of dresses we didn't try."}]},{"cues":[{"time":788373,"text":"CA: What sort of things?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":790454,"text":"JS: Well, everything."},{"time":791636,"text":"Everything is grist for the mill --\nexcept hem lengths."},{"time":796852,"text":"Weather, annual reports,"},{"time":799176,"text":"quarterly reports, historic data itself,\nvolumes, you name it."},{"time":803932,"text":"Whatever there is."},{"time":805107,"text":"We take in terabytes of data a day."},{"time":807752,"text":"And store it away and massage it\nand get it ready for analysis."},{"time":813446,"text":"You're looking for anomalies."},{"time":814852,"text":"You're looking for -- like you said,"},{"time":817829,"text":"the efficient market\nhypothesis is not correct."}]},{"cues":[{"time":820305,"text":"CA: But any one anomaly\nmight be just a random thing."},{"time":823796,"text":"So, is the secret here to just look\nat multiple strange anomalies,"},{"time":827478,"text":"and see when they align?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":829238,"text":"JS: Any one anomaly\nmight be a random thing;"},{"time":832475,"text":"however, if you have enough data\nyou can tell that it's not."},{"time":835538,"text":"You can see an anomaly that's persistent\nfor a sufficiently long time --"},{"time":840512,"text":"the probability of it being\nrandom is not high."},{"time":845511,"text":"But these things fade after a while;\nanomalies can get washed out."},{"time":850393,"text":"So you have to keep on top\nof the business."}]},{"cues":[{"time":852837,"text":"CA: A lot of people look\nat the hedge fund industry now"},{"time":855533,"text":"and are sort of ... shocked by it,"},{"time":859955,"text":"by how much wealth is created there,"},{"time":862151,"text":"and how much talent is going into it."},{"time":865523,"text":"Do you have any worries\nabout that industry,"},{"time":869553,"text":"and perhaps the financial\nindustry in general?"},{"time":871991,"text":"Kind of being on a runaway train that's --"},{"time":874719,"text":"I don't know --\nhelping increase inequality?"},{"time":878773,"text":"How would you champion what's happening\nin the hedge fund industry?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":882628,"text":"JS: I think in the last\nthree or four years,"},{"time":885260,"text":"hedge funds have not done especially well."},{"time":887387,"text":"We've done dandy,"},{"time":888811,"text":"but the hedge fund industry as a whole\nhas not done so wonderfully."},{"time":892836,"text":"The stock market has been on a roll,\ngoing up as everybody knows,"},{"time":897762,"text":"and price-earnings ratios have grown."},{"time":901231,"text":"So an awful lot of the wealth\nthat's been created in the last --"},{"time":904318,"text":"let's say, five or six years --\nhas not been created by hedge funds."},{"time":908458,"text":"People would ask me,\n\"What's a hedge fund?\""},{"time":911703,"text":"And I'd say, \"One and 20.\""},{"time":913987,"text":"Which means -- now it's two and 20 --"},{"time":917577,"text":"it's two percent fixed fee\nand 20 percent of profits."},{"time":920954,"text":"Hedge funds are all\ndifferent kinds of creatures."}]},{"cues":[{"time":923330,"text":"CA: Rumor has it you charge\nslightly higher fees than that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":927339,"text":"JS: We charged the highest fees\nin the world at one time."},{"time":930444,"text":"Five and 44, that's what we charge."}]},{"cues":[{"time":933694,"text":"CA: Five and 44."},{"time":935116,"text":"So five percent flat,\n44 percent of upside."},{"time":938374,"text":"You still made your investors\nspectacular amounts of money."}]},{"cues":[{"time":941181,"text":"JS: We made good returns, yes."},{"time":942657,"text":"People got very mad:\n\"How can you charge such high fees?\""},{"time":945681,"text":"I said, \"OK, you can withdraw.\""},{"time":947332,"text":"But \"How can I get more?\"\nwas what people were --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":950174,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":951702,"text":"But at a certain point,\nas I think I told you,"},{"time":954166,"text":"we bought out all the investors\nbecause there's a capacity to the fund."}]},{"cues":[{"time":959365,"text":"CA: But should we worry\nabout the hedge fund industry"},{"time":962093,"text":"attracting too much of the world's\ngreat mathematical and other talent"},{"time":967555,"text":"to work on that, as opposed\nto the many other problems in the world?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":970817,"text":"JS: Well, it's not just mathematical."},{"time":972770,"text":"We hire astronomers and physicists\nand things like that."},{"time":975833,"text":"I don't think we should worry\nabout it too much."},{"time":978288,"text":"It's still a pretty small industry."},{"time":981454,"text":"And in fact, bringing science\ninto the investing world"},{"time":987475,"text":"has improved that world."},{"time":989658,"text":"It's reduced volatility.\nIt's increased liquidity."},{"time":993752,"text":"Spreads are narrower because\npeople are trading that kind of stuff."},{"time":996965,"text":"So I'm not too worried about Einstein\ngoing off and starting a hedge fund."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1002478,"text":"CA: You're at a phase in your life now\nwhere you're actually investing, though,"},{"time":1006666,"text":"at the other end of the supply chain --"},{"time":1010424,"text":"you're actually boosting\nmathematics across America."},{"time":1014552,"text":"This is your wife, Marilyn."},{"time":1016441,"text":"You're working on\nphilanthropic issues together."},{"time":1021221,"text":"Tell me about that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1022408,"text":"JS: Well, Marilyn started --"},{"time":1026081,"text":"there she is up there,\nmy beautiful wife --"},{"time":1029552,"text":"she started the foundation\nabout 20 years ago."},{"time":1032548,"text":"I think '94."},{"time":1033723,"text":"I claim it was '93, she says it was '94,"},{"time":1035842,"text":"but it was one of those two years."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1038437,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1040596,"text":"We started the foundation,\njust as a convenient way to give charity."},{"time":1048346,"text":"She kept the books, and so on."},{"time":1050877,"text":"We did not have a vision at that time,\nbut gradually a vision emerged --"},{"time":1057615,"text":"which was to focus on math and science,\nto focus on basic research."},{"time":1063569,"text":"And that's what we've done."},{"time":1066365,"text":"Six years ago or so, I left Renaissance\nand went to work at the foundation."},{"time":1072744,"text":"So that's what we do."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1074339,"text":"CA: And so Math for America\nis basically investing"},{"time":1077272,"text":"in math teachers around the country,"},{"time":1079934,"text":"giving them some extra income,\ngiving them support and coaching."},{"time":1083760,"text":"And really trying\nto make that more effective"},{"time":1086835,"text":"and make that a calling\nto which teachers can aspire."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1089460,"text":"JS: Yeah -- instead of beating up\nthe bad teachers,"},{"time":1094274,"text":"which has created morale problems\nall through the educational community,"},{"time":1099151,"text":"in particular in math and science,"},{"time":1101616,"text":"we focus on celebrating the good ones\nand giving them status."},{"time":1107770,"text":"Yeah, we give them extra money,\n15,000 dollars a year."},{"time":1110725,"text":"We have 800 math and science teachers\nin New York City in public schools today,"},{"time":1115216,"text":"as part of a core."},{"time":1117054,"text":"There's a great morale among them."},{"time":1120764,"text":"They're staying in the field."},{"time":1123294,"text":"Next year, it'll be 1,000\nand that'll be 10 percent"},{"time":1126213,"text":"of the math and science teachers\nin New York [City] public schools."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1129781,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1135710,"text":"CA: Jim, here's another project\nthat you've supported philanthropically:"},{"time":1139144,"text":"Research into origins of life, I guess."},{"time":1141565,"text":"What are we looking at here?"},{"time":1143536,"text":"JS: Well, I'll save that for a second."},{"time":1145442,"text":"And then I'll tell you\nwhat you're looking at."},{"time":1147628,"text":"Origins of life is a fascinating question."},{"time":1150708,"text":"How did we get here?"},{"time":1153170,"text":"Well, there are two questions:"},{"time":1154965,"text":"One is, what is the route\nfrom geology to biology --"},{"time":1160857,"text":"how did we get here?"},{"time":1162262,"text":"And the other question is,\nwhat did we start with?"},{"time":1164650,"text":"What material, if any,\ndid we have to work with on this route?"},{"time":1167776,"text":"Those are two very,\nvery interesting questions."},{"time":1171773,"text":"The first question is a tortuous path\nfrom geology up to RNA"},{"time":1177631,"text":"or something like that --\nhow did that all work?"},{"time":1179913,"text":"And the other,\nwhat do we have to work with?"},{"time":1182325,"text":"Well, more than we think."},{"time":1184120,"text":"So what's pictured there\nis a star in formation."},{"time":1189836,"text":"Now, every year in our Milky Way,\nwhich has 100 billion stars,"},{"time":1193285,"text":"about two new stars are created."},{"time":1195804,"text":"Don't ask me how, but they're created."},{"time":1198298,"text":"And it takes them about a million\nyears to settle out."},{"time":1202132,"text":"So, in steady state,"},{"time":1204332,"text":"there are about two million stars\nin formation at any time."},{"time":1208204,"text":"That one is somewhere\nalong this settling-down period."},{"time":1212067,"text":"And there's all this crap\nsort of circling around it,"},{"time":1215027,"text":"dust and stuff."},{"time":1217479,"text":"And it'll form probably a solar system,\nor whatever it forms."},{"time":1220526,"text":"But here's the thing --"},{"time":1222726,"text":"in this dust that surrounds a forming star"},{"time":1229098,"text":"have been found, now,\nsignificant organic molecules."},{"time":1235958,"text":"Molecules not just like methane,\nbut formaldehyde and cyanide --"},{"time":1242121,"text":"things that are the building blocks --\nthe seeds, if you will -- of life."},{"time":1249136,"text":"So, that may be typical."},{"time":1252395,"text":"And it may be typical\nthat planets around the universe"},{"time":1259353,"text":"start off with some of these\nbasic building blocks."},{"time":1263830,"text":"Now does that mean\nthere's going to be life all around?"},{"time":1266569,"text":"Maybe."},{"time":1267957,"text":"But it's a question\nof how tortuous this path is"},{"time":1272108,"text":"from those frail beginnings,\nthose seeds, all the way to life."},{"time":1276526,"text":"And most of those seeds\nwill fall on fallow planets."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1281742,"text":"CA: So for you, personally,"},{"time":1283175,"text":"finding an answer to this question\nof where we came from,"},{"time":1285921,"text":"of how did this thing happen,\nthat is something you would love to see."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1289603,"text":"JS: Would love to see."},{"time":1291413,"text":"And like to know --"},{"time":1292927,"text":"if that path is tortuous enough,\nand so improbable,"},{"time":1298121,"text":"that no matter what you start with,\nwe could be a singularity."},{"time":1303336,"text":"But on the other hand,"},{"time":1304512,"text":"given all this organic dust\nthat's floating around,"},{"time":1308014,"text":"we could have lots of friends out there."},{"time":1312947,"text":"It'd be great to know."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1314132,"text":"CA: Jim, a couple of years ago,\nI got the chance to speak with Elon Musk,"},{"time":1317636,"text":"and I asked him the secret of his success,"},{"time":1320497,"text":"and he said taking\nphysics seriously was it."},{"time":1324696,"text":"Listening to you, what I hear you saying\nis taking math seriously,"},{"time":1328723,"text":"that has infused your whole life."},{"time":1332123,"text":"It's made you an absolute fortune,\nand now it's allowing you to invest"},{"time":1336710,"text":"in the futures of thousands and thousands\nof kids across America and elsewhere."},{"time":1341567,"text":"Could it be that science actually works?"},{"time":1344449,"text":"That math actually works?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1347245,"text":"JS: Well, math certainly works.\nMath certainly works."},{"time":1351641,"text":"But this has been fun."},{"time":1352863,"text":"Working with Marilyn and giving it away\nhas been very enjoyable."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1357833,"text":"CA: I just find it --\nit's an inspirational thought to me,"},{"time":1360793,"text":"that by taking knowledge seriously,\nso much more can come from it."},{"time":1364824,"text":"So thank you for your amazing life,\nand for coming here to TED."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1367866,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1368651,"text":"Jim Simons!"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1369806,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}